# UI Construction

This rule covers the structural and stylistic conventions for writing Thunderstorm UI: how components are named, how SCSS is organised, how design tokens are applied, and how state management integrates with layout. For prohibited HTML elements and infra utilities see [ui-components.mdc](ui-components.mdc). For component boundaries and the three-tier hierarchy see [ui-component-granularity.mdc](ui-component-granularity.mdc).

---

## 1. Component type naming

Give every component a type-prefix that declares its architectural role. The prefix is the first thing a reader sees — it tells them what kind of thing this is before they read a single line.

| Prefix | Role |
|--------|------|
| `Page_` | Full-page owner. Mounts in a route. Owns workspace layout, module-to-state wiring, edit/view mode orchestration. |
| `Manager_` | WorkHub slot. Composes panels and editors for one domain object. Receives context from WorkHub. |
| `Editor_` | Focused edit surface for one domain entity. Owns `EditableDBItemV3`, tab structure, and save logic. |
| `Renderer_` | Renders a sub-section in read or edit mode. Receives an `editable` prop and/or `editMode` flag. Never independently routed. |
| `Panel_` | A vertical slice of a workspace (list, detail, filter). Receives selection state from its parent. |
| `Component_` | Self-contained, reusable, feature-complete unit with its own internal state. Domain-agnostic. |
| `Header_` | Title bar for an entity view — back navigation, title, action buttons. |
| `Dialog_` | Modal content. Co-located with its trigger. |
| `Field_` | One atomic form field: label + input + validation, bound to one prop of an editable. |

**Pattern:** `[Prefix]_[Domain][SubDomain]` — PascalCase, underscored separator.

```
Page_ProjectEditor
Manager_Article
Editor_Article
Renderer_ArticleStateEditor
Panel_ArticleList
Header_ArticleState
Dialog_ConfirmDelete
Field_ArticleTitle
```

The file name matches the class/function name exactly. The SCSS file uses the same base name.

