## 3. Design token discipline

### Colors — your app's token namespace

Every project defines a color token module. Import it under a consistent alias (convention: `C`) and use it exclusively. **Never write a hex value or `rgb()` directly in component SCSS.**

```scss
@use '@your-app/styles/color' as C;

// Correct
color:        C.$text-primary;
border-color: C.$border-subtle;
background:   C.red(4);    // if your token system provides palette functions

// Wrong
color:      #4f4f4f;
border:     1px solid #e3e9f2;
background: #f6f8fc;
```

**No local color variables.** Do not define `$font-color: #333` or `$border: #e3e9f2` inside a component SCSS file. A color that appears locally belongs in the design system — find the right token or add one.

### Mixins — `@nu-art/ts-styles`

Use the `S` namespace for all interaction and utility mixins. Never write raw hover/active chains by hand.

```scss
@use '@nu-art/ts-styles' as S;

@include S.mouse-interactive-background(C.$surface-hover, C.$surface-active);
@include S.mouse-interactive-text(C.$text-primary, C.$text-on-accent);
@include S.color-svg(C.$icon-primary);
@include S.mouse-interactive-icon(C.$icon-primary);
@include S.text-ellipsis;
@include S.customScrollbar('vertical', true);
```

### Inline styles

The only acceptable use of `style={{}}` in TSX is for values that come from runtime data — a color stored in a database record, a dynamically computed pixel measurement. Never use it for design decisions.

```tsx
// Correct — value is data
<div style={{ background: entity.colorHex }} />

// Wrong — design decision belongs in SCSS
<div style={{ padding: '30px', gap: '10px' }} />
```

When a child component needs a style override in a specific parent context, **do not add a new class to the child** and do not use inline styles. Instead, scope the override through the parent's existing class in SCSS:

```scss
// Correct — parent's class scopes the child override
.page__sampling-dashboard {
  .component__video-header { gap: var(--space-3); }
}

// Wrong — adding a new class to the child just for this context
.component__video-header.compact-header { gap: var(--space-3); }

// Wrong — inline style override in TSX
<Component_VideoHeader style={{ gap: 'var(--space-3)' }} />
```

Only introduce a new class on the child if the override represents a genuinely reusable variant that multiple parents would use.

