## 5. Layout primitives — always use them

Never write `display: flex; flex-direction: column` or `display: flex; align-items: center` on a raw `<div>`. Import and use the layout primitives from `@nu-art/thunderstorm-frontend`:

| Component | Alignment | Use for |
|-----------|-----------|---------|
| `LL_V_L` | column, left | Default vertical stack |
| `LL_V_C` | column, center | Centered column |
| `LL_H_C` | row, center | Horizontal row, vertically centered |
| `LL_H_T` | row, top | Row with items of differing height |
| `LL_H_B` | row, bottom | Row pinned to bottom |
| `LL_VH_C` | both axes, center | Full-height/width centered container |
| `Grid` | CSS grid | Any grid layout |

```tsx
// Correct
<LL_H_C className={'header__article-state'}>
  <LL_V_L className={'header__article-state__info'}>
    <h2>{title}</h2>
  </LL_V_L>
</LL_H_C>

// Wrong
<div style={{ display: 'flex', alignItems: 'center' }}>
  <div style={{ display: 'flex', flexDirection: 'column' }}>
```

All layout primitives accept `className` and all standard `div` props.

