## 6. File and folder organisation

### Co-location

```
Page_SamplingDashboard/
  Page_SamplingDashboard.tsx
  Page_SamplingDashboard.scss   ← always co-located, always the same base name
  Component_TargetCard.tsx      ← enclosed component used only by this page
  Component_TargetCard.scss
  consts.scss                   ← only when siblings share placeholders
  types.ts                      ← shared types for this component family
```

One SCSS file per TSX file. A pure-composition component with no styles needs no `.scss` file.

### Component placement

- **Enclosed components** — used only by one parent — live in the parent's folder.
- **Shared components** — used by multiple pages/parents — live in a sibling folder named after the domain: `{domain}-widgets/` or `{domain}-components/`.

```
ui/
  Page_SamplingDashboard/
    Page_SamplingDashboard.tsx
    Component_TargetCard.tsx       ← only used by this page
  Page_VideoStudio/
    Page_VideoStudio.tsx
  video-widgets/                   ← shared across multiple pages
    Component_VideoHeader.tsx
    Component_VideoMetrics.tsx
    Component_SamplingStats.tsx
```

Do not create generic folder names (`widgets/`, `components/`, `shared/`). The folder name must carry the domain context.

### Import order

```scss
@use '@nu-art/ts-styles' as S;         // 1. Thunderstorm mixins
@use '@your-app/styles/color' as C;    // 2. App color tokens
@use '@your-app/styles/design' as *;   // 3. App design placeholders (if needed)
@use './consts' as *;                  // 4. Local family consts (if exists)
```

**Never use `@import`** — it is deprecated in modern SCSS and causes duplication. Always `@use`.

**Never use `as *` for external packages.** Wildcard imports on anything outside the current component family hide where names come from. Use explicit aliases for all external packages; `as *` is only acceptable for a local `consts.scss` whose full contents you own.

