## 8. EditableDBItemV3 — construction pattern

For full rules on when and why to use `EditableDBItemV3`, see [editable-item-pattern.mdc](editable-item-pattern.mdc). This section covers only how to chain it correctly at component construction time.

**Auto-save editor** (form fields save on change/blur):

```tsx
private buildEditable(id: UniqueId): EditableDBItemV3<DBProto_SomeEntity> {
  const item = ModuleFE_SomeEntity.cache.unique(id);
  if (!item)
    throw new BadImplementationException(`Item not found: ${id}`);

  return new EditableDBItemV3(item, ModuleFE_SomeEntity)
    .setAutoSave(true)
    .setDebounceTimeout(200)
    .setOnChanged(async () => this.forceUpdate())
    .setOnSaveCompleted(() => this.forceUpdate());
}
```

**Explicit-save editor** (user clicks Save):

```tsx
private buildEditable(item: DB_SomeEntity): EditableDBItemV3<DBProto_SomeEntity> {
  return new EditableDBItemV3(item, ModuleFE_SomeEntity)
    .setAutoSave(false);
}

private onSave = async () => {
  if (!this.canSave()) return;
  await this.state.editable.save();
  this.props.functions.deselect();
};
```

