## 10. Tabs — typed identifiers, never string arrays

Tab UIDs and selector option lists must use string literal union types or typed constants. Never use raw string arrays.

```tsx
// Correct
type ArticleTab = 'general' | 'metadata' | 'history';

const tabs: Tab[] = [
  { uid: 'general',  title: 'General',  content: () => <Editor_Article_General  editable={editable} /> },
  { uid: 'metadata', title: 'Metadata', content: () => <Editor_Article_Metadata editable={editable} /> },
  { uid: 'history',  title: 'History',  content: () => <Editor_Article_History  editable={editable} /> },
];

// Wrong
const tabOptions = ['General', 'Metadata', 'History'];
```

