## 11. SCSS-specific prohibited patterns

The HTML element prohibitions (`<button>`, `<select>`, `<label>`, `<span>`) and routing (`window.location`) are in [ui-components.mdc](ui-components.mdc). The following are SCSS and structure violations not covered there:

| Pattern | Why banned | Correct approach |
|---------|-----------|-----------------|
| `#id` as component root | Collides with `openContent` pop-up anchors; non-reusable | Class selector per naming scheme above |
| Hardcoded hex / `rgb()` in SCSS | Breaks design system; un-themeable | App color token namespace |
| Local `$font-color`, `$border` etc. | Duplicates design system | Find/add the right token |
| `@import` in SCSS | Deprecated; causes duplication | `@use` with alias |
| `as *` on external packages | Hides origin of names | Explicit alias; `as *` only for local `consts.scss` |
| `!important` | Specificity war symptom | Restructure SCSS scope |
| `display: flex` on raw `<div>` | Bypasses layout primitives | `LL_H_C`, `LL_V_L`, etc. |
| Inline styles for appearance | See [ui-component-granularity.mdc](ui-component-granularity.mdc) | SCSS class |
| Direct entity mutation without `EditableDBItemV3` | Bypasses concurrency control | `EditableDBItemV3` |
| String arrays for tabs or option lists | No type safety, no completion | String literal union |

