## 12. SCSS specificity — how overrides work

All SCSS is global — there are no CSS modules. Specificity is managed through scope, not isolation.

**The contract:**

- Library component SCSS defines structure with low specificity (one class deep).
- The Page/Manager applies design via `@extend %AppDesign_*` within its own root scope — the ancestor class adds one level of specificity, which wins cleanly.
- Never target library component internals from an unrelated component's scope.

```scss
// Correct — ancestor scope wins cleanly
.manager__article {
  .ts-dropdown { @extend %AppDesign_DropDown; }
}

// Wrong — unrelated scope reaching into library internals
.some-other-component .ts-dropdown { color: red; }
```

When one specific instance needs an override beyond the base design (e.g. a wider dropdown in one context), add a modifier class in TSX and scope the override under it:

```scss
.manager__article {
  .ts-dropdown.wide-picker { width: 400px; }
}
```

Never escalate to `!important` to win a specificity conflict — that signals the scope structure is wrong and needs to be fixed.

---

## 13. Self-check — signals of non-compliant code

| Signal in code | What is wrong | What it should be |
|----------------|--------------|-------------------|
| `#some-component-root { }` | ID as component root | `.manager__some-component { }` |
| `$font-color: #4f4f4f;` at top of SCSS | Local design token | App token from `C` namespace |
| `.parent__child__grandchild__great-grandchild` flat chain | Over-deep BEM instead of nesting | SCSS nesting with shorter element names |
| `<div style={{ display: 'flex', alignItems: 'center' }}>` | Raw flex layout | `<LL_H_C>` |
| `<div style={{ padding: '20px', gap: '8px' }}>` | Inline design | SCSS class |
| `color: #4f4f4f` in SCSS | Hardcoded color | App color token |
| `const options = ['Foo', 'Bar', 'Baz']` driving a tab/selector | Untyped string list | String literal union type |
| `@import '...'` in SCSS | Deprecated import | `@use` with alias |
| `EditableDBItemV2` or direct `module.cache.unique() + setState` | Old entity editing | `EditableDBItemV3` with `.setAutoSave().setOnChanged()` |
| `if (!editMode) return <A>; else return <B>;` ad-hoc branching | Undeclared mode pattern | `Component_SwitchView` or `disabled` prop |
| `// #### Section ####` banner comments | Noise; signals class is too large | Decompose into smaller components |
| `!important` anywhere | Specificity conflict | Fix the scope |
